Omega Pharma Spends 2.75 Million Euros on Additional Buybacks

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-10-11T16:27:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/omega-pharma-spends-2-75-million-euros-on-additional-buybacks.html
Omega Pharma (OME)  NV said it spent almost
2.75 million euros buying back an additional 80,729 own shares
in on- and off-market transactions in the period from Oct. 3
through Oct. 11, according to an e-mailed statement.  Omega Pharma, which is subject to a 36 euros-a-share buyout
offer from Couckinvest NV, now holds 13.5 percent of its
outstanding share count, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Martens at 
 jmartens1@bloomberg.net  